      "title": "Improve version-related query parameters",
      "url": "https://github.com/JKRhb/sdf-semantic-references/pull/2",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "JKRhb",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Since I noticed that the current approach of using a single `version` parameter with concepts such as the caret notation, this PR fans out the single `version` parameter into multiple ones which allow for more fine-grained of minimal and maximal version numbers. The new approach also supports versioning formats that do not adhere to the semantic versioning format with a major, minor, and patch version number.\r\n\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-03T12:01:10Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-03T12:14:41Z",
